<% @title = "How to make a request" %>

<%= render :partial => 'sidebar' %>
<div id="left_column_flip">

  <h1><%= @title %></h1>

  <p>To make a request through <%= site_name %> follow the steps below:<p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <p><strong>Step 1</strong>: Enter the name of the institution the requestor claimed that keeps the information or select from the list of public institutions.</p>
      <p>Once the information of the institution is displayed click on: <strong>Make a request to this authority</strong></p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p><strong>Step 2</strong>: Make sure the information you need is not available in the page for transparency of the institution website. Authorities in Panama are required to publish certain information online. <a href="http://www.antai.gob.pa/publicaciones/Ley-6-de-22-enero-2002.pdf">Article 9, 10, 11, 26 and 27 of Law 6 of 2002</a></p>
      <p>You may also review applications that have been answered. It is likely that another user has requested the same information earlier. (This could save you a lot of time)</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p><strong>Step 3</strong>: In the small box write "General Subject of your request."
      In the larger box type your request in simple, clear language, ask for specific documents or information. This website is not intended for general inquiries.</p>
      <p>A request for information through this platform does not have a formality as such, but must contain a minimum of requirements based on <a href="http://www.antai.gob.pa/publicaciones/Ley-6-de-22-enero-2002.pdf">Article 5 of Transparency Law 6</a>.</p>
      <p>The system will request the following minimum of requirements at the time of registration:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Name of the requestor</li>
        <li>Personal identity number</li>
        <li>Residential or office address</li>
        <li>The telephone number where you can be reached.</li>
      </ol>
      <p>In the case of legal persons, must be detailed enrollment data and personal data from your legal representative.</p>
      <p>* (Registered users will not need to enter this information to make the request because it was collected at registration)</p>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Step 4</strong>: Check your request this will prevent the same to be rejected by absence of requirements, if you want to change something click on <strong>Edit Request</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Step 5</strong>: To submit your request click on <strong>Send Request</strong> once you have submitted your request the system will automatically generated the request sending an email to the information officer of the public institution.</li>
    <li><strong>Step 6</strong>: Wait for the request for a maximum of 30 calendar days.</li>

  <div id="hash_link_padding"></div>

</div>
